==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fraught
<hw>Fraught</hw> <pr>(fr⟦add⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE.<ets>fraight</ets>, <ets>fraght</ets>; akin to Dan.
<ets>fragt</ets>, Sw. <ets>frakt</ets>, D. <ets>vracht</ets>, G.
<ets>fracht</ets>, cf. OHG. <ets>fr⟦emac⟧ht</ets> merit, reward; perh.
from a pref. corresponding to E. <ets>for</ets> + The root of E.
<ets>own</ets>. Cf. <er>Freight</er>.]</ety> <def>A freight; a
cargo.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fraught</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fraught
<hw>Fraught</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Freighted; laden; filled; stored;
charged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A vessel of our country richly <qex>fraught</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A discourse <qex>fraught</qex> with all the commending excellences
of speech.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Enterprises <qex>fraught</qex> with world-wide benefits.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fraught</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fraught
<hw>Fraught</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Fraughted</conjf> or <conjf>Fraught</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Fraughting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to Dan.
<ets>fragte</ets>, Sw. <ets>frakta</ets>, D. <ets>bevrachten</ets>, G.
<ets>frachten</ets>, cf. OHG. <ets>fr⟦emac⟧ht⟦omac⟧n</ets> to deserve.
See <er>Fraught</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To freight; to load; to
burden; to fill; to crowd.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Upon the tumbling billows <qex>fraughted</qex> ride⟦br⟧
The armed ships.</q> <rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

